title: Suicide Squad: Kill the Justice League Review
author: @chuggyman5606
comment: Everyone seems to forget the massive backlash rocksteady faced when Arkham Knight launched. The red flags were planted in 2015. Everyone wants to put on rose tinted glasses and pretend the original Arkham trilogy was flawless. the reality is that rocksteady faced many criticisms with Arkhm Knights launch. Everyone was disappointed how much Batmobile gameplay there was, everyone was disappointed how bad the boss fights were after coming off City and Origins, everyone hated the predictable twist, and the game launched with a $60 season pass that everyone heavily criticized, saying it was the same price as the base game. Rocksteady promised everyone it would be worth the price. And how did this turn? We got a 10 minute red hood dlc, a 10 minute Harley Quinn dlc, a 90 minute batgirl campaign and a 20 minute mister freeze side mission.

King shark was the only likable member of the squad who respected the heroes. Such a waste of 7 years development time. We couldve gotten a batman beyond/ justice league/ gotham knights. But no. Instead we get to play as anti heroes/ villains. Devs got what they wanted by surprising us. Surprised us that they could fall so low from their own legacy of batman. Just to meet his end by a gun . author: @P1X3LAB
comment:
Readers & viewers, don't forget this is the same channel/company that gave Nickelodeon All star brawl 2 a 9 out of 10. A game that is basically dead now. Guardians of the galaxy was overlooked as a game due to the same publicity issues and it was a great game. IGN sadly has very little credibility to me as they should to many as well. What works for me won't work for them and vice versa. Games nowadays are torn apart and there's always something missing.
Since they had to buy the game to review it, they low balled it. When it's sponsored, they over rate it. Trends don't lie. We need to be aware of trying to be steered away from something fun just cause its missing something someone else wants. IGN - start buying ALL games you review and then tell us what you really think ü§î
